      "Recoverable depreciation is the portion of your claim that the insurance company holds back initially. They will pay the \"actual cash value\" of your roof upfront, minus your deductible. Once the work is completed, you submit the final invoice and they release the remaining depreciation. Do not forget this step. It can be thousands of dollars.",
